foreign tokyobased act the lead had one hit single akuma ga kureta aoi bara blue rose but the project soon fell apart when two american members of the group were deported in  merrill signed a solo management deal with watanabe productions who contracted him to atlantic records and changed his professional surname from sachs pronounced sax to merrill because merrill sounded less lascivious and was more commercially viable when spoken by young japanese pop music fans he recorded one album with atlantic records alone in tokyo  which yielded one hit single namida teardrops and he became the first foreign domestic market pop star in the japanese group sounds merrill acted on the popular tv soap opera jikan desu yo and had his own corner as a regular on the tbss young  a morning show for teens he was the featured principal as a model in ads for nissan cars jun clothing annann nonno and gt jeans in  he released an lp of his own compositions titled merrill  in japan for denoncolumbia record label produced by mickey curtis at the peak of his fame tiny tim covered an alan merrill composition from the merrill  album a song titled movies in  on scepter records he then formed the band vodka collins which became japans top glam rock act the band included japanese superstars hiroshi monsieur kamayatsu and hiroshi oguchi vodka collins recorded one lp in  titled tokyo – new york on the emi toshiba label which is still available today in cd reissues the band are best known for recording and releasing the first popular glam rock songs in japanese in  the double asided single sands of time and automatic pilot professional career in londonedit in  in london merrill formed the band arrows as lead singer and bass guitarist with drummer paul varley and guitarist jake hooker peter meaden was the arrows first manager but later they signed with mickie mosts rak records in march  the arrows were in the top  in the uk charts with the song touch too much arrows became a popular band with teens and once again merrill had slid back into the teen market he had fought hard to get out of in japan arrows had another hit single with my last night with you which made the uk top  in  but the bands single releases were few and far between as a result of their producer mickie mosts winding down his own career momentum recorded at morgan studio in london  alan merrill played bass guitar on drummer cozy powells chart hit single the man in black and the bside after dark produced by mickie most on rak records the recording made a peak position of  in the british charts with arrows merrill sang three chart hit records as the bands lead singer all produced by mickie most touch too much   uk charts toughen up   uk charts and my last night with you   uk charts they made one more single that would be an important one i love rock n roll  a song that started out as a bside to the  rpm arrows single broken down heart the song i love rock n roll was composed by alan merrill and arrows bandmate jake hookercitation needed the record was later flipped to aside status and the band got only one tv performance with the song the shows producer muriel young was so impressed with arrows that she made a pitch to granada itv for them to have their own television series arrows got their own weekly tv series arrows in  taking over the bay city rollers granada tv series shangalang the band arrows signed with mam management their producer mickie most was so angry at the band for signing the management deal that he vowed to never release another arrows record so it came to pass that arrows had their own weekly tv series and no records released during that time their ratings were so good that they got a second weekly series but they released no new recordings arrows disbanded shortly after the end of the second series in  merrill married fashion model cathee dahmen and formed a new group the albumoriented rock act runner with steve gould rare bird mick feat van morrison band and dave dowle whitesnake the runner album charted in the billboard top  in the united statescitation needed later professional careeredit in  merrill joined forces with rick derringer as a guitaristvocalist in new york city they recorded three albums good dirty fun live at the ritz rick derringer and friends and a film the rick derringer rock spectacular  alan merrill wrote three songs on the rick derringer good dirty fun album white heat alan merrill shake me alan merrilljake hooker and lesson learned alan merrillrick derringer shake me was included in the soundtrack of the film where the boys are  in  joan jett released a cover of the arrows song i love rock n roll composed by alan merrill and jake hooker it went to number one in the us billboard charts for  weeks the following year lou rawls recorded alan merrills song when the night comes as the title track of his  epic records album the rawls version of the song was taken into space by astronaut guion bluford the first music taken to and played in outer space in  merrill recorded a solo album for polydor records simply titled alan merrill a collection of selfcomposed tracks some friends contributing to this record were steve winwood mick taylor and dallas taylor it was released in  and received critical acclaim in  merrill joined the meat loaf band for the promotional tour of his blind before i stop album and stayed for several years recording meat loafs  live at wembley  album for arista records in  merrill was offered a role in the television series encyclopedia brown on hbo and was a part of the successful series in his role as principal character casey sparkz merrill wrote a song for the production who done it  which he performed in the film and was featured in the concert scene in  a vodka collins reunion tour was organized due to popular demand as a result of the successful cd reissue of their debut vinyl lp tokyonew york the tokyobased band toured japan then several years later recorded the first in a series of reunion albums chemical reaction  which was followed by pink soup  boys life  and boys in the band  the vodka collins tokyonew york album has been reissued again as recently as october  on emi japancitation needed current activityedit in recent years merrill has released solo albums never pet a burning dog  cupid deranged  a merrilly christmas  double shot rocks   a tribute to songwriters otis blackwell and arthur alexander aleecat  at the candy shop  rive gauche   a tribute to the left banke the reissue alien in tokyo ep single hard road and an in concert album the aleecat live in japan were all released in  new albums by mr merrill titled the face of   numbers  snakes and ladders  songer singerwriter  and arrows th anniversary edition  were recently released the arrows  top  uk hit touch too much featuring lead vocals by alan merrill appears on the soundtrack of the feature film the look of love a  biopic of london legend paul raymond restless soul a song merrill cowrote with shinohara nobuhiko  that was on air nightly on the asahi tv travel show sekai no kaido wo yuku traveling on the roads of the world in japan broadcast from  the arrows songs we can make it together and moving next door to you composed by merrill and jake hooker were used on the bbc tv show homes under the hammer series  episode  and series  episode   respectively in england first airdate was february   the songs were bsides of the arrows rak records top  hit singles touch too much  and my last night with you  produced by mickie most in  and  with lead vocals by alan merrill in september  merrill added his guitar parts to popular japanese vocalist superflys cover of his composition i love rock n roll released three months later on warner brothersjapan records in early june  he released a duet with fellow s uk rock star bob bradbury of the band hello titled brothers in rock and another duet this one in japanese with bruce bauer hello japan out june   on september   he released a song solo album demo graphic he also does live concerts internationally both with backing bands and solo acoustic a film featuring alan merrill as a principal actor was released july st  titled reagitator  revenge of the parody   he currently resides in new york city referencesedit  gee mister japan rock age  thealeecatcom retrieved    a b outsight radio hours interview  february  archiveorg retrieved march     darren paltrowitz alanmerrillinterview thealeecatcom retrieved    alan merrill profile allmusiccom retrieved    interview helen merrill part  jazzwaxcom  retrieved    remembering aaron sachs forumsaxonthewebnet retrieved    alan merrill milano  when mosquitos ruled the earth alanmerrilltumblrcom  retrieved    merrilly merrilly we go — in  new york city there was a band called the merrillymerillywegotumblrorg retrieved    jetcom  prices drop as you shop jetcom retrieved    the lead nippopcom archived from the original on  retrieved    allan merrill  alone in tokyo vinyl lp album discogscom  retrieved    alan merrill interview tumblr retrieved    tiny tim  am i just another pretty facemovies discogscom retrieved    vodka collins profile nippopcom archived from the original on  retrieved    vodka collins  new york tokyo discogscom retrieved    tokyonew york  vodka collins  songs reviews credits allmusic retrieved    arrows  discography discogscom retrieved    cozy powell the man in black sessions alanmerrilltumblrcom  retrieved    arrows songs • top songschart singles discography • music vf us  uk hits charts musicvfcom retrieved    the arrows enduring legacy  from bill harrys rock n pop shop alanmerrillcom retrieved    rick derringer  good dirty fun discogscom retrieved    live at the ritz new york  rick derringer  credits allmusic retrieved    king biscuit flower hour presents rick derringer  friends oldiescom retrieved    rick derringer  rock spectacular discogscom retrieved    alan merrill imdbcom retrieved    lomography  today in history  joan jett and the blackhearts’ cover of ‘i love rock ‘n’ roll’ peaks at  on billboard hot  and stays there for the next six weeks billboardcom retrieved    lou rawls when the night comes  imgurcom retrieved    when the night comes by lou rawls rateyourmusiccom retrieved  permanent dead link  live at wembley  meat loaf  credits allmusic retrieved    encyclopedia brown imdbcom january     alan merrill  who done it discogs retrieved    vodka collins discogscom retrieved    alan merrill  cd baby music store cdbabycom retrieved    the look of love imdbcom july     alan merrill  restless soul lyrics letssingitcom  retrieved    sekai no kaido wo iku original soundtrack original soundtrack cd album cdjapancojp  retrieved    arrows we can make it together homes under the hammer bbc youtube retrieved    arrows moving next door to you homes under the hammmer youtube  retrieved    arrows   touch too much discogscom retrieved    arrows   my last night with you discogscom retrieved    david knights  arrows singer alan merrill performs at korks in otley ilkleygazettecouk retrieved    superfly に「saikko」なrrのカバー  spice  エンタメメディア スパイス spiceeplusjp retrieved    brothers in rock  single by bob bradbury  alan merrill on apple music itunesapplecom retrieved    ♫ hello japan  bruce bauer listen cdbaby cdbabycom retrieved september     edgy edgy edgy — sunday sept th  first preview exclusive lifeonaledgetumblrcom retrieved    ♫ demo graphic  alan merrill listen cdbaby cdbabycom retrieved    sachs allan alanmerrillcom alanmerrillcom retrieved    httpwwwimdbcomtitlett external linksedit alan merrill on imdb vodka collins official website vodka collins infosite arrows website allmusic whos who in japanese rock  alan merrill with the band the lead  authority control worldcat identities viaf  musicbrainz debcccfcfea retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlealanmerrilloldid categories american male singersamerican rock musicianssongwriters from new york birthsliving peoplepeople from the bronxneverland express membersamerican expatria